{"id": 223695466, "title": "XL Bully battle in Scots street as riot cops arrest two women", "text": "Riot cops scrambled to a street in Dundee after reports of a fight between two XL Bullies. Officers were alerted to the incident at Cardoss Place in the city at around 6:30pm last night, Saturday, May 25. Two women have been charged under the Dangerous Dogs Act and two dogs \u2018removed to kennels\u2019 following the incident. A report will now be sent to the Procurator Fiscal in due course. The dogs are understood to be XL Bullies, which are officially a banned breed \u2013 meaning owners are required to follow strict rules. Speaking to The Courier, local residents described seeing a woman covered in blood as riot police descended on the street. One neighbour claims they were told by police to go inside their homes after they spotted a woman \u201ccovered in blood\u201d. Another man, who did not wish to be named, claimed he saw a young child trying to separate two dogs who started fighting. He commented: \u201cIt was scary scenes that unfolded here on Saturday night. A child was trying to help separate these two XL Bully-style dogs, he was hysterical. \u201cThis could have ended in an absolute tragedy. \u201cOne woman\u2019s jacket turned red with blood as she tried to separate these dogs.\u201d Another local said it was \u201cmayhem\u201d before police arrived. He said: \u201cIt was mayhem. It was literally like a scene from Shameless. When the police arrived we were told to get back inside our homes. \u201cIt\u2019s scary what went down here on Saturday. It could have ended in a tragedy.\" A Police Scotland spokesperson said: \u201cWe were called around 6.30pm on Saturday, May 25, to a report of two dogs fighting in the Cardross Place area of Dundee. \u201cOfficers attended and two women, aged 53 and 36, were charged in connection with the Dangerous Dogs Act. \u201cA report will be sent to the Procurator Fiscal. \u201cThe dogs were removed to kennels.\" Don't miss the latest news from around Scotland and beyond. Sign up to our daily newsletter .", "summary": "The two women were charged for offences under the Dangerous Dogs Act.", "url": "https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/xl-bully-battle-scots-street-32896270", "image": "https://i2-prod.dailyrecord.co.uk/incoming/article32657882.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_XL-Bullies-Being-Walked-On-Private-Land-After-Ban.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:21:39", "author": "John-Paul Clark", "authors": ["John-Paul Clark"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.865}